I see this is in the spec, but I couldn't get this parameter to work. If it is a valid parameter,
I'd be curious about why it's included or how it's used (is it stored somewhere, etc.?).
Reproduction using the template set up earlier:
POST /_index_template/_simulate_index/myindex-1?cause=foo

Returns:
{
  "error" : {
    "root_cause" : [
      {
        "type" : "illegal_argument_exception",
        "reason" : "request [/_index_template/_simulate_index/myindex-1] contains unrecognized parameter: [cause]"
      }
    ],
    "type" : "illegal_argument_exception",
    "reason" : "request [/_index_template/_simulate_index/myindex-1] contains unrecognized parameter: [cause]"
  },
  "status" : 400
}

